1
00:01:26,375 --> 00:01:30,207
In B.E. 2483,

2
00:01:31,000 --> 00:01:33,832
the nation descended into a dark age.

3
00:01:34,957 --> 00:01:37,417
People struggled with great adversity.

4
00:01:38,417 --> 00:01:40,500
The bureaucracy was corrupt.

5
00:01:41,750 --> 00:01:44,417
Rumors about the next world war

6
00:01:45,082 --> 00:01:46,667
and Japan's plans for invasion

7
00:01:47,667 --> 00:01:49,832
had people living in terror.

8
00:01:50,667 --> 00:01:52,917
The government continued
its nationalist propaganda

9
00:01:53,500 --> 00:01:57,082
while the whole country

10
00:01:57,792 --> 00:02:01,292
was falling apart.
All hell was breaking loose.

11
00:02:01,707 --> 00:02:07,457
Failed by legal systems,
the oppressed chose the life of banditry.

12
00:02:07,625 --> 00:02:11,957
New cliques and gangs emerged.
Criminals could be found everywhere.

13
00:02:12,832 --> 00:02:15,417
One of the most notorious outlaws

14
00:02:15,832 --> 00:02:17,625
was an ethnic separatist

15
00:02:18,082 --> 00:02:20,875
named Alhawi Yalu.

16
00:02:21,207 --> 00:02:24,832
Master of sorcery. Local people called him

17
00:02:25,375 --> 00:02:27,750
the devil of Budo mountain.

18
00:02:32,500 --> 00:02:35,207
Police Lt. Khun Puntharak Rajjadej,

19
00:02:35,917 --> 00:02:39,542
I called you here today
because I wanted to ask you a favor

20
00:02:41,750 --> 00:02:43,957
regarding the Budo mountain case.

21
00:02:45,707 --> 00:02:48,417
Alhawi Yalu is getting more powerful.

22
00:02:49,417 --> 00:02:52,957
He almost has the whole
mountain area under control.

23
00:02:54,957 --> 00:02:59,042
I want to send you undercover
for half a year.

24
00:02:59,792 --> 00:03:05,082
Once the new inspector arrives,
your job is done.

25
00:03:06,082 --> 00:03:08,292
You understand the conditions?

26
00:03:11,292 --> 00:03:12,457
Yes, sir.

27
00:03:14,375 --> 00:03:15,875
Since it's a secret mission,

28
00:03:16,957 --> 00:03:18,582
no backup.

29
00:03:20,375 --> 00:03:21,542
This means...

30
00:03:23,625 --> 00:03:24,750
I may not come back.

31
00:03:26,250 --> 00:03:27,792
Criminals are everywhere

32
00:03:28,917 --> 00:03:32,167
and yet we can't bring them to justice.

33
00:03:33,375 --> 00:03:34,875
This is our fate now.

34
00:03:35,457 --> 00:03:37,542
We can't tell what will happen next

35
00:03:38,457 --> 00:03:40,957
or who we will become.

36
00:03:45,082 --> 00:03:48,457
Do you think you can change that?

37
00:03:57,542 --> 00:03:59,542
BUDO MOUNTAIN

38
00:04:01,667 --> 00:04:03,207
Alhawi's army

39
00:04:03,875 --> 00:04:06,500
spreads out across the region.

40
00:04:07,375 --> 00:04:08,667
His left and right-hand men,

41
00:04:09,292 --> 00:04:11,125
also with great knowledge of sorcery,

42
00:04:11,625 --> 00:04:13,125
are as dangerous as their master.

43
00:04:14,707 --> 00:04:15,665
Suea Sang...

44
00:04:15,750 --> 00:04:17,541
SUEA SANG

45
00:04:18,583 --> 00:04:19,833
...and Suea Grub Kamtong.

46
00:04:19,916 --> 00:04:21,041
SUEA GRUB KAMTONG

47
00:04:24,250 --> 00:04:28,416
May 11, B.E. 2483,

48
00:04:29,666 --> 00:04:32,375
my unit, led by Inspector Issara,

49
00:04:33,625 --> 00:04:36,333
was going to dismantle
Suea Grub Kamtong's gang.

50
00:04:38,083 --> 00:04:42,333
Instead, we were surrounded
by his henchmen.

51
00:04:42,958 --> 00:04:44,166
Inspector Issara was shot.

52
00:04:47,041 --> 00:04:48,291
Inspector, let me see.

53
00:04:55,500 --> 00:04:57,708
Dammit! Aren't they tired of firing?

54
00:04:57,833 --> 00:04:59,541
Hey! Hey!

55
00:05:04,083 --> 00:05:05,000
Stop!

56
00:05:13,500 --> 00:05:17,125
This is the police! Come out!
We have you surrounded.

57
00:05:20,208 --> 00:05:22,083
Am I going to see my child?

58
00:05:25,625 --> 00:05:29,125
I still don't know
what to name him. Any ideas?

59
00:05:29,833 --> 00:05:30,958
Name?

60
00:05:31,833 --> 00:05:32,708
What about Joy?

61
00:05:33,833 --> 00:05:36,040
-Joy?
-Hey, it's a good name.

62
00:05:36,125 --> 00:05:37,291
Enough with that!

63
00:05:37,875 --> 00:05:39,083
I need cigarettes.

64
00:05:41,541 --> 00:05:43,666
Hey! Do you have some?

65
00:05:44,375 --> 00:05:46,166
-This is the last pack.
-Throw it over.

66
00:05:47,916 --> 00:05:49,665
Ugh, what a terrible throw!

67
00:05:49,750 --> 00:05:51,166
-Go get it.
-Yes, sir.

68
00:05:53,208 --> 00:05:54,500
Cover me! Cover me!

69
00:05:57,208 --> 00:05:59,083
Go help him. I'll cover you.

70
00:06:04,125 --> 00:06:05,166
Go!

71
00:06:14,458 --> 00:06:16,666
Deputy, they're coming in closer.

72
00:06:17,333 --> 00:06:18,791
They intend to block us in.

73
00:06:19,875 --> 00:06:21,083
We're not gonna make it.

74
00:06:26,375 --> 00:06:28,125
Look! Kids over there.

75
00:06:28,500 --> 00:06:30,333
I'll cover. You go help them.

76
00:06:34,791 --> 00:06:37,291
I'll go. You cover me.

77
00:06:38,916 --> 00:06:39,791
Noon!

78
00:06:46,166 --> 00:06:47,666
We just want Khun Pun.

79
00:06:48,500 --> 00:06:51,875
-Come out, or I'll kill them all.
-Lieutenant, you heard him.

80
00:06:52,250 --> 00:06:54,041
If you don't go out, we'll die.

81
00:07:07,875 --> 00:07:09,208
That's me. Khun Pun.

82
00:07:12,333 --> 00:07:13,458
YANTRA TATTOOS

83
00:07:18,000 --> 00:07:19,083
Noon!

84
00:07:22,458 --> 00:07:23,708
Noon!

85
00:07:38,083 --> 00:07:39,125
Fire in the hole!

86
00:08:49,957 --> 00:08:52,832
I take refuge in Buddha.

87
00:08:53,332 --> 00:08:55,292
I take refuge in Dharma.

88
00:08:55,625 --> 00:08:58,875
I take refuge in Sangha.

89
00:08:59,082 --> 00:09:03,832
Bless me with the power of the mind.

90
00:09:05,625 --> 00:09:08,375
What should we do? They got the inspector.

91
00:09:14,500 --> 00:09:15,707
How many bullets?

92
00:09:16,332 --> 00:09:18,000
-I have four.
-I have three.

93
00:09:19,167 --> 00:09:21,000
All right then. I'm going to help him.

94
00:09:21,625 --> 00:09:24,707
I'll run towards them.
You follow my signals and shoot.

95
00:09:25,000 --> 00:09:26,292
-Understood?
-Yes, sir!

96
00:09:43,667 --> 00:09:46,792
-Lieutenant, stop right there!
-One more step,

97
00:09:47,167 --> 00:09:49,082
I'll blow his brains out.

98
00:10:01,707 --> 00:10:04,207
Bullets were flying everywhere.

99
00:10:04,707 --> 00:10:06,207
I lost many officers.

100
00:10:06,707 --> 00:10:09,875
At that point, I thought
I had to surrender myself.

101
00:10:10,375 --> 00:10:13,542
He had a gun pointed to my head.
He was going to pull the trigger.

102
00:10:15,375 --> 00:10:16,500
What were you thinking?

103
00:10:16,957 --> 00:10:18,667
I could have been killed!

104
00:10:25,417 --> 00:10:26,917
This hurts so damn much.

105
00:10:38,500 --> 00:10:42,750
Inspector Issara was praised
for taking down Suea Grub's gang.

106
00:10:43,082 --> 00:10:46,957
He pulled enough strings to get promoted

107
00:10:47,167 --> 00:10:49,000
and got sent back to Bangkok.

108
00:10:53,792 --> 00:10:54,792
Meanwhile,

109
00:10:55,207 --> 00:10:56,707
I'm on my way to meet him.

110
00:10:57,750 --> 00:10:58,875
Alhawi Yalu.

111
00:11:17,207 --> 00:11:21,582
Beards that turn to copper
and livers that turn to iron.

112
00:11:22,332 --> 00:11:26,667
Things like these are very powerful,

113
00:11:27,292 --> 00:11:30,125
and can only be in the possession
of true masters,

114
00:11:30,750 --> 00:11:32,750
the perfected ones.

115
00:11:34,500 --> 00:11:35,457
How did you get them?

116
00:11:39,125 --> 00:11:40,250
None of your business.

117
00:11:42,332 --> 00:11:46,957
There's still a tooth in the roof of
the mouth to complete the sacred trinity.

118
00:12:37,750 --> 00:12:38,832
Venerable sir,

119
00:12:40,792 --> 00:12:42,332
did you know

120
00:12:43,792 --> 00:12:45,582
I ordered my men to dig up your past?

121
00:12:46,792 --> 00:12:47,750
I know that

122
00:12:50,082 --> 00:12:51,082
you were a cop.

123
00:13:14,957 --> 00:13:17,957
The one thing I don't have yet,

124
00:13:19,500 --> 00:13:20,750
it's in your mouth.

125
00:13:21,667 --> 00:13:25,375
People who know sorcery
can still be killed by a lance, right?

126
00:13:26,707 --> 00:13:27,582
So...

127
00:13:28,707 --> 00:13:29,792
your tooth,

128
00:13:34,332 --> 00:13:35,457
just let me have it.

129
00:13:59,417 --> 00:14:03,542
I've been thinking over and over
about running for election.

130
00:14:04,207 --> 00:14:07,417
-Well, I'm interested.
-If you do,

131
00:14:08,707 --> 00:14:12,000
I'm sure you can win.
You don't have to worry at all.

132
00:14:12,542 --> 00:14:18,957
As long as you ignore what's going on
regarding our opium trade.

133
00:14:20,082 --> 00:14:21,207
Sir,

134
00:14:21,457 --> 00:14:23,417
are you trying
to bribe a government official?

135
00:14:24,417 --> 00:14:27,082
L... Luang, sir...

136
00:14:31,000 --> 00:14:32,082
Luang, sir,

137
00:14:34,000 --> 00:14:35,500
by the way,

138
00:14:36,042 --> 00:14:41,542
I heard that they're sending
the new inspector general to station here.

139
00:14:48,375 --> 00:14:51,125
I'm afraid--

140
00:14:52,167 --> 00:14:57,625
You know this is a remote area.
Who would bother inspecting anything?

141
00:14:58,125 --> 00:15:01,000
It's full of bandits and criminals.

142
00:15:29,082 --> 00:15:30,417
PUBLIC SECURITY POLICE

143
00:16:05,625 --> 00:16:06,750
Hey!

144
00:16:23,792 --> 00:16:28,375
On September 13, Luang Phadej,
the newly assigned inspector

145
00:16:29,250 --> 00:16:32,500
was attacked by Alhawi's guerrillas.

146
00:16:33,457 --> 00:16:37,667
Almost the whole unit was killed.
Only two could make it out.

147
00:16:55,792 --> 00:17:01,625
Come and hear me,
The story of our hometown...

148
00:17:01,957 --> 00:17:05,500
I was trying to reach out to
the two officers but to no avail.

149
00:17:06,291 --> 00:17:12,291
I have no idea what happened to them
or what's going to happen to me.

150
00:17:13,041 --> 00:17:14,250
My guess is that

151
00:17:14,750 --> 00:17:18,125
the government loses credibility
and way too much money for this.

152
00:17:19,416 --> 00:17:22,375
There will be no reinforcements
after the attack.

153
00:17:23,833 --> 00:17:28,125
I'm on my own. Nobody
gives a damn about this town.

154
00:17:28,958 --> 00:17:35,416
Nobody wants to come near a place
where everyone is an outlaw.

155
00:17:35,791 --> 00:17:39,875
I will withdraw from this mission
if I can answer this for myself:

156
00:17:40,708 --> 00:17:43,750
what made them choose to be criminals

157
00:17:44,458 --> 00:17:47,208
and what made me choose to be a policeman?

158
00:17:48,208 --> 00:17:50,333
I guess Mali likes you, But.

159
00:17:54,208 --> 00:17:59,416
Amidst the sea,
I watch the moon at night.

160
00:18:00,125 --> 00:18:06,291
It reminds me of my love who is far away.

161
00:18:46,375 --> 00:18:49,458
Did my horse scare off your fish?

162
00:18:55,041 --> 00:18:56,208
No, sir.

163
00:18:57,583 --> 00:18:59,416
Even if your horse comes down to the pond,

164
00:19:00,916 --> 00:19:02,333
the fish won't take the bait.

165
00:19:03,750 --> 00:19:05,291
There's just small fish in this pond.

166
00:19:06,333 --> 00:19:08,875
But master, I heard that

167
00:19:10,333 --> 00:19:11,583
there's this giant fish in here.

168
00:19:12,541 --> 00:19:13,458
Goatherder,

169
00:19:14,333 --> 00:19:17,083
you plan to catch
a giant fish with this tiny hook?

170
00:19:20,125 --> 00:19:21,958
I just want to see it.

171
00:19:22,875 --> 00:19:26,083
Even if I have to dive, I'd do it.

172
00:19:27,250 --> 00:19:29,041
Every part of the Budo mountain range

173
00:19:29,458 --> 00:19:30,708
is under my protection.

174
00:19:31,666 --> 00:19:35,166
But go on. You are allowed
to catch some fish.

175
00:19:38,875 --> 00:19:40,208
This is my bet.

176
00:19:42,375 --> 00:19:45,708
If you can catch a big fish
with that tiny hook of yours,

177
00:19:49,750 --> 00:19:50,625
you can keep it.

178
00:19:52,000 --> 00:19:54,416
But if you can't, the next time I see you,

179
00:19:55,166 --> 00:19:57,416
I'm gonna need that back.

180
00:19:58,875 --> 00:19:59,916
Yes, master.

181
00:20:20,458 --> 00:20:22,416
SUB-DISTRICT KUANLAY POLICE STATION

182
00:20:26,208 --> 00:20:27,916
Let's go!

183
00:20:29,375 --> 00:20:33,791
-Inspector!
-What's going on?

184
00:20:36,708 --> 00:20:41,791
Mr. Oo told the police that Kheaw
and Samae abducted and raped his daughter.

185
00:20:42,458 --> 00:20:44,875
I chased after them
and brought them here, sir.

186
00:20:54,041 --> 00:20:55,000
Hey!

187
00:20:55,583 --> 00:20:57,000
How much have you got?

188
00:20:57,875 --> 00:20:59,625
-Two baht.
-You?

189
00:20:59,833 --> 00:21:00,833
Five baht.

190
00:21:01,875 --> 00:21:02,958
Hand it over.

191
00:21:09,375 --> 00:21:10,333
Here, Inspector.

192
00:21:13,958 --> 00:21:14,833
So broke.

193
00:21:20,291 --> 00:21:22,416
Keep the money. It's a reparation.

194
00:21:23,625 --> 00:21:24,708
You can go home now.

195
00:21:28,916 --> 00:21:31,041
Inspector, how can you do that?

196
00:21:31,750 --> 00:21:34,666
Bang, lock him up until he calms down.

197
00:21:36,625 --> 00:21:41,250
Bang! I'm an officer!
The suspects are standing right there!

198
00:21:43,000 --> 00:21:43,875
Bang!

199
00:21:55,250 --> 00:21:56,375
Who do you think you are?

200
00:22:04,250 --> 00:22:05,125
Phueak.

201
00:22:08,208 --> 00:22:11,750
Those two work for the Ivory Club.

202
00:22:12,291 --> 00:22:15,375
Luang Olan's men. If we arrest them,

203
00:22:16,083 --> 00:22:18,208
Mr. Oo's family won't be alive tomorrow.

204
00:22:28,333 --> 00:22:29,208
Do you understand?

205
00:22:32,875 --> 00:22:38,583
Remember, you work for me now.
Do as I say. No questions asked.

206
00:22:38,708 --> 00:22:42,250
I'm going to keep
your payments for two months.

207
00:22:42,666 --> 00:22:45,166
That's a hundred baht
for an acceptance fee.

208
00:22:46,041 --> 00:22:48,583
I'll introduce you as my distant relative.

209
00:22:49,208 --> 00:22:53,833
Don't tell anyone you're not
from around here. Just keep quiet.

210
00:22:53,958 --> 00:22:56,541
Especially with the locals.
Stay in your lane. Understand?

211
00:22:56,875 --> 00:23:00,083
Keep your head down, your mouth shut.
Otherwise, you're gonna get killed.

212
00:23:00,291 --> 00:23:05,541
That's it. Oh, let's push.

213
00:23:06,000 --> 00:23:09,916
Good. You have to pay me for this.
Another month of your payment.

214
00:23:12,541 --> 00:23:14,916
Go away!

215
00:23:15,083 --> 00:23:19,333
Go away! Shoo!

216
00:23:23,000 --> 00:23:26,791
Please, Monsieur le Consul.
I am so honored.

217
00:23:27,250 --> 00:23:28,666
Hello, Mr. Paul.

218
00:23:29,708 --> 00:23:34,791
This is monsieur Jean Pierre,
the consul of France.

219
00:23:39,041 --> 00:23:41,750
Thank you for your invitation, Mr. Olan.

220
00:23:42,250 --> 00:23:44,375
You are such a great host.

221
00:23:45,791 --> 00:23:49,666
Do you know anything
about the spies in Thailand?

222
00:23:50,791 --> 00:23:55,040
There're plenty of boats
in the Gulf of Thailand.

223
00:23:55,125 --> 00:23:59,583
Most of them belong to the Chinese,
not the Japanese.

224
00:24:00,458 --> 00:24:04,666
I take it you're exhausted
from the long journey.

225
00:24:05,416 --> 00:24:08,208
I've prepared
some pretty masseuses for you.

226
00:24:08,708 --> 00:24:13,291
-You take such a good care of me. Cheers.
-Cheers.

227
00:25:04,666 --> 00:25:05,625
You have a lighter?

228
00:25:13,708 --> 00:25:14,583
You can keep it.

229
00:25:18,375 --> 00:25:19,291
Thanks.

230
00:25:26,083 --> 00:25:27,958
Wow! But!

231
00:25:29,083 --> 00:25:31,541
You look so handsome in this uniform.

232
00:25:32,583 --> 00:25:35,125
-Khaitoh took you to work then?
-Yes.

233
00:25:35,291 --> 00:25:36,916
Let's go to the club.

234
00:25:37,750 --> 00:25:39,375
I'm about to go on stage.

235
00:25:40,083 --> 00:25:41,166
Want to watch?

236
00:25:42,083 --> 00:25:45,625
-I don't think I can do that.
-It's all right. Come with me.

237
00:25:46,166 --> 00:25:48,250
The show is about to begin.

238
00:25:56,875 --> 00:26:03,833
The moon shines bright
On the shore at night

239
00:26:06,291 --> 00:26:09,458
Lights up the sky

240
00:26:10,333 --> 00:26:13,958
How beautiful

241
00:26:14,625 --> 00:26:21,583
Cool breezes whisper as river flows

242
00:26:22,916 --> 00:26:29,875
The soft sounds wander
Under the moonlight

243
00:26:31,083 --> 00:26:35,125
Hear the birds sing

244
00:26:35,250 --> 00:26:40,458
Deep in the woods
Whose song is this?

245
00:26:43,416 --> 00:26:47,833
Oh, it belongs
To the night birds and cicadas

246
00:26:48,583 --> 00:26:52,750
Happily they perform

247
00:26:53,875 --> 00:26:58,583
Sweet smells the wind brings

248
00:26:58,666 --> 00:27:03,500
From flowers as the birds sing

249
00:27:04,041 --> 00:27:09,250
Their song helps me remind myself

250
00:27:09,583 --> 00:27:14,125
That love awaits

251
00:27:16,208 --> 00:27:23,208
The moon shines bright
On the shore at night

252
00:27:24,708 --> 00:27:28,916
What will happen next

253
00:27:30,791 --> 00:27:35,791
I don't know

254
00:27:46,708 --> 00:27:48,125
You did a wonderful job tonight.

255
00:27:49,791 --> 00:27:51,458
You don't have to say that.

256
00:28:00,916 --> 00:28:01,791
Why wouldn't I?

257
00:28:36,708 --> 00:28:37,666
Why did they do it?

258
00:28:38,333 --> 00:28:40,750
Don't you know?
His rice fields were seized.

259
00:28:41,416 --> 00:28:43,125
Those two rascals from the club

260
00:28:43,625 --> 00:28:45,041
raped Hong, his daughter.

261
00:28:46,416 --> 00:28:50,333
Hong was dead, so Luea hung herself.

262
00:28:52,708 --> 00:28:53,875
Take them to the temple.

263
00:29:13,333 --> 00:29:14,375
Tell me right now.

264
