529
01:04:23,375 --> 01:04:24,250
No.

530
01:04:25,916 --> 01:04:27,041
To be honest,

531
01:04:27,875 --> 01:04:29,000
you're more than capable,

532
01:04:29,916 --> 01:04:32,583
perhaps a lot more than Alhawi even.

533
01:04:33,375 --> 01:04:34,666
Why be just a follower?

534
01:04:36,000 --> 01:04:37,125
Hear me out.

535
01:04:38,625 --> 01:04:39,625
From now on,

536
01:04:40,375 --> 01:04:42,458
you take orders from me directly.

537
01:04:43,791 --> 01:04:44,833
What do you say?

538
01:04:47,708 --> 01:04:48,583
All right.

539
01:04:49,916 --> 01:04:50,791
Sir.

540
01:04:59,458 --> 01:05:01,000
Welcome to the civil world.

541
01:05:05,208 --> 01:05:07,708
This is mother turtle's home.

542
01:05:08,916 --> 01:05:10,958
Mother turtle has three eggs.

543
01:05:11,875 --> 01:05:13,500
Father turtle's walking out.

544
01:05:15,000 --> 01:05:17,583
I think I'm going to write a song.

545
01:05:17,958 --> 01:05:18,958
What is it about?

546
01:05:19,791 --> 01:05:23,375
About little Mali

547
01:05:23,958 --> 01:05:27,708
and Malai, my sister. Little Mali flowers
braided into beautiful Malai.

548
01:05:28,833 --> 01:05:30,083
Make it beautiful.

549
01:05:30,541 --> 01:05:33,500
Of course. That's my specialty.

550
01:05:40,833 --> 01:05:41,708
Mali!

551
01:05:44,416 --> 01:05:47,583
Mali!

552
01:05:50,291 --> 01:05:53,166
Mali!

553
01:05:55,083 --> 01:05:58,000
Here is mother turtle.

554
01:06:00,541 --> 01:06:02,666
Brother, come play with me?

555
01:06:05,666 --> 01:06:08,458
Mother turtle will lay eggs here.

556
01:07:07,791 --> 01:07:08,750
Damn.

557
01:07:20,500 --> 01:07:21,666
We were too late.

558
01:07:24,208 --> 01:07:25,250
-Bang.
-Yes?

559
01:07:25,541 --> 01:07:27,833
-Phueak, gather the bodies.
-Yes, sir.

560
01:07:29,500 --> 01:07:30,625
Do it now.

561
01:07:42,083 --> 01:07:44,500
Inspector!
This one's still alive.

562
01:07:50,333 --> 01:07:52,041
Suea Sang attacked us.

563
01:07:54,666 --> 01:07:57,583
Khaitoh and some villagers fled
to the jungle.

564
01:07:58,541 --> 01:07:59,416
Tuan!

565
01:08:06,958 --> 01:08:07,916
Khun Pun.

566
01:08:09,125 --> 01:08:10,208
Khun Pun.

567
01:08:27,332 --> 01:08:28,250
In the morning,

568
01:08:28,500 --> 01:08:30,500
the tide is highest.
If we sail along the mountain,

569
01:08:30,625 --> 01:08:33,457
we can arrive on the shore
without worrying about the sandbar.

570
01:08:33,917 --> 01:08:34,917
Yes, sir! Admiral, sir!

571
01:08:35,625 --> 01:08:38,082
Send my message to the Army.

572
01:08:38,750 --> 01:08:41,000
Tell them to prepare for landings.

573
01:08:41,707 --> 01:08:43,917
Tomorrow our Imperial Japanese Army

574
01:08:44,582 --> 01:08:47,167
will prove our greatness
and conquer this land.

575
01:08:48,082 --> 01:08:50,082
-Yes, sir! Admiral, sir!
-Yes, sir! Admiral, sir!

576
01:08:52,875 --> 01:08:55,125
-Hello.
-Hello.

577
01:08:56,582 --> 01:08:58,250
What's the progress with our trains?

578
01:08:58,875 --> 01:09:01,875
About our trains, what's the progress?

579
01:09:02,707 --> 01:09:05,625
Tell him the trains will arrive tomorrow.

580
01:09:06,000 --> 01:09:08,375
Everything is going as planned.

581
01:09:08,792 --> 01:09:11,375
Just don't forget to keep
your end of the bargain.

582
01:09:12,582 --> 01:09:14,832
The trains will arrive here tomorrow.

583
01:09:16,375 --> 01:09:21,042
Everything is in progress
just as you ordered.

584
01:09:21,832 --> 01:09:25,707
You just keep your end of the bargain
like we agreed.

585
01:09:27,582 --> 01:09:29,375
We have plenty of gold. Don't you worry.

586
01:09:31,375 --> 01:09:35,417
Well, I have to worry about my 20%.

587
01:09:36,707 --> 01:09:37,582
Your country...

588
01:09:39,292 --> 01:09:41,125
is so cheap for us to buy.

589
01:10:05,957 --> 01:10:09,875
-Sir?
-Glum, Malai, come out now.

590
01:10:15,250 --> 01:10:16,207
How's the village?

591
01:10:27,417 --> 01:10:28,707
We have to go through the jungle.

592
01:10:30,082 --> 01:10:32,167
Once we reach the border,

593
01:10:33,625 --> 01:10:34,750
we'll find the main railroad.

594
01:10:35,582 --> 01:10:36,792
There should be passing trains.

595
01:10:37,667 --> 01:10:38,542
By that time,

596
01:10:39,957 --> 01:10:42,917
we should be safe.

597
01:10:43,875 --> 01:10:45,542
Come on now. Let's go.

598
01:10:46,375 --> 01:10:47,292
Careful.

599
01:10:48,832 --> 01:10:51,167
-Watch your step. It's slippery.
-Careful.

600
01:10:54,542 --> 01:10:55,417
Wait!

601
01:11:10,000 --> 01:11:11,167
You have to hurry.

602
01:11:12,082 --> 01:11:13,375
Suea Sang is coming.

603
01:11:16,625 --> 01:11:17,500
Go!

604
01:11:23,167 --> 01:11:25,500
Bu-nga, come with us.

605
01:11:27,125 --> 01:11:28,957
This is all I can do for you, Malai.

606
01:11:31,375 --> 01:11:32,250
Take care.

607
01:11:38,957 --> 01:11:41,500
Malai! Malai! Come on!

608
01:11:52,125 --> 01:11:53,000
Hurry!

609
01:12:27,500 --> 01:12:28,417
Come on now!

610
01:12:30,957 --> 01:12:32,332
Let's go!

611
01:12:36,457 --> 01:12:39,582
Hurry!

612
01:12:48,250 --> 01:12:49,125
Come on! Come on!

613
01:13:57,000 --> 01:13:59,667
Promise me that Mali didn't die in vain.

614
01:14:02,417 --> 01:14:03,375
I promise.

615
01:14:08,417 --> 01:14:10,125
-Inspector.
-Yes, sir.

616
01:14:10,957 --> 01:14:13,707
When the trains arrive in Ampoe,
everyone should be safe.

617
01:14:15,292 --> 01:14:16,625
I will go back to town.

618
01:14:17,667 --> 01:14:19,250
Take care of them.

619
01:14:21,750 --> 01:14:22,667
Sir,

620
01:14:25,500 --> 01:14:28,667
how can you be an inspector
without subordinates?

621
01:14:29,957 --> 01:14:32,832
-I'm going with you.
-Me too.

622
01:14:34,207 --> 01:14:35,125
Me too.

623
01:14:48,750 --> 01:14:49,957
It's Suea Sang, sir.

624
01:14:51,457 --> 01:14:53,707
Kill them all!

625
01:15:09,457 --> 01:15:11,792
Sir, can you please tell me the marks?

626
01:15:11,957 --> 01:15:12,917
Two o'clock.

627
01:15:16,207 --> 01:15:17,625
Four o'clock.

628
01:15:54,792 --> 01:15:58,042
Get out of the way! Go!

629
01:16:05,250 --> 01:16:07,000
Hurry!

630
01:16:12,417 --> 01:16:13,750
We surrender!

631
01:16:18,250 --> 01:16:19,957
-Don't shoot.
-Get down!

632
01:16:34,250 --> 01:16:35,125
Put the guns down.

633
01:18:54,582 --> 01:18:55,875
Khun Pun!

634
01:18:57,667 --> 01:19:01,917
-Khun Pun!
-But! But!

635
01:19:08,957 --> 01:19:10,082
No!

636
01:19:15,875 --> 01:19:18,917
No!

637
01:19:42,500 --> 01:19:44,167
Serve me as your master.

638
01:23:42,000 --> 01:23:43,125
Get down!

639
01:24:58,792 --> 01:24:59,707
Hey!

640
01:25:01,082 --> 01:25:02,042
What happened?

641
01:25:03,082 --> 01:25:03,957
Who did this?

642
01:25:07,375 --> 01:25:08,457
Suea Sang.

643
01:25:09,375 --> 01:25:11,082
He took his people to kill the villagers.

644
01:25:16,167 --> 01:25:18,207
How could he? It wasn't my order!

645
01:25:39,042 --> 01:25:41,957
The soldiers on the train
were all Japanese.

646
01:25:45,875 --> 01:25:46,832
Khun Pun.

647
01:26:10,500 --> 01:26:12,292
I can only come with you this far.

648
01:26:24,332 --> 01:26:25,457
I'm going with you.

649
01:26:28,582 --> 01:26:31,667
Master, you made me a promise.

650
01:26:33,832 --> 01:26:34,707
Alhawi.

651
01:26:39,542 --> 01:26:40,707
You betrayed me.

652
01:26:46,042 --> 01:26:46,957
Alhawi.

653
01:26:48,207 --> 01:26:49,167
Where are you?

654
01:26:51,125 --> 01:26:52,000
You...

655
01:26:53,542 --> 01:26:55,582
didn't do it for everyone
like you promised.

656
01:26:57,250 --> 01:26:58,207
Alhawi.

657
01:26:58,917 --> 01:27:00,457
It's just a little misunderstanding.

658
01:27:02,917 --> 01:27:05,542
Suea Sang turned against me
because of you!

659
01:27:08,457 --> 01:27:10,750
Because you failed to kill Khun Pun,

660
01:27:11,417 --> 01:27:12,917
you left me with no choice!

661
01:27:13,707 --> 01:27:14,625
Alhawi,

662
01:27:15,332 --> 01:27:19,375
sometimes we have to make sacrifices
for the greater good.

663
01:27:20,667 --> 01:27:25,250
Luang! You are a bloodsucker!

664
01:27:31,875 --> 01:27:35,957
-Go!
-Get out of here.

665
01:27:40,832 --> 01:27:41,875
Come this way.

666
01:27:42,667 --> 01:27:43,542
Come on!

667
01:27:49,375 --> 01:27:50,542
Go! Go!

668
01:27:54,417 --> 01:27:55,332
Go!

669
01:28:06,500 --> 01:28:07,957
What's going on here?

670
01:28:08,582 --> 01:28:10,582
You snake!

671
01:28:10,917 --> 01:28:13,792
Are you on our side or what?

672
01:28:14,500 --> 01:28:15,500
Listen, I can explain.

673
01:28:50,582 --> 01:28:51,707
I'm out of ammo.

674
01:28:53,625 --> 01:28:54,625
Fall back!

675
01:29:29,707 --> 01:29:31,125
Come on! Run!

676
01:29:31,417 --> 01:29:32,457
Hurry!

677
01:29:34,707 --> 01:29:35,582
Come here!

678
01:29:50,582 --> 01:29:51,500
Inspector!

679
01:29:53,292 --> 01:29:55,542
Inspector!

680
01:30:14,000 --> 01:30:14,875
Get down!

681
01:31:17,917 --> 01:31:18,792
Malai...

682
01:31:28,625 --> 01:31:29,917
No!

683
01:31:36,542 --> 01:31:37,875
Malai!

684
01:31:59,167 --> 01:32:02,332
-Phueak, cover me!
-Yes, sir!

685
01:33:55,417 --> 01:33:57,207
If you promise to quit being a criminal,

686
01:34:00,582 --> 01:34:01,792
I'll take you alive.

687
01:34:09,625 --> 01:34:10,667
What about you?

688
01:34:12,292 --> 01:34:14,582
Do you still want to catch that big fish?

689
01:34:52,250 --> 01:34:53,332
Both of us...

690
01:34:54,542 --> 01:34:56,082
are wasting time fighting each other.

691
01:34:58,042 --> 01:34:59,707
Give yourself up, Alhawi.

692
01:35:00,375 --> 01:35:04,292
Luang Olan manipulated and used you.
I'll be your witness in court.

693
01:35:06,250 --> 01:35:07,292
Two hundred people.

694
01:35:08,917 --> 01:35:11,875
I have killed two hundred people.

695
01:35:15,125 --> 01:35:16,832
Most of them were cops.

696
01:35:19,250 --> 01:35:20,125
And you?

697
01:35:21,375 --> 01:35:22,582
How many have you killed?

698
01:35:24,582 --> 01:35:25,917
Bet it's no less than mine.

699
01:35:26,500 --> 01:35:27,375
Right?

700
01:35:31,417 --> 01:35:33,000
We have both been used.

701
01:35:34,917 --> 01:35:37,000
We are both going to hell.

702
01:35:40,082 --> 01:35:41,500
You should just be yourself.

703
01:35:42,707 --> 01:35:43,792
Admit it,

704
01:35:45,207 --> 01:35:47,457
you're dying to cut off my head.

705
01:35:50,375 --> 01:35:52,000
Come and take your future...

706
01:35:53,792 --> 01:35:54,917
in exchange for your heart...

707
01:35:56,832 --> 01:35:58,582
that I'll gouge out with my bare hands.

708
01:36:06,250 --> 01:36:07,167
Right.

709
01:36:08,792 --> 01:36:10,167
Perhaps you and I,

710
01:36:11,292 --> 01:36:13,000
we're not so different after all,

711
01:36:13,375 --> 01:36:14,292
Alhawi.

712
01:36:58,167 --> 01:36:59,500
Raya Gaji,

713
01:37:01,167 --> 01:37:03,375
another name of Alhawi?

714
01:37:04,417 --> 01:37:06,792
He's a legendary fighter...

715
01:37:08,417 --> 01:37:10,042
who never lost his faith.

716
01:37:12,292 --> 01:37:16,000
Young man, I can see
the spirit of Raya Gaji within you.

717
01:37:17,000 --> 01:37:19,832
Please bring my son back
from the endless abyss.

718
01:38:07,582 --> 01:38:09,167
Alhawi's weakness...

719
01:38:10,707 --> 01:38:11,750
is his heart.

720
01:38:16,957 --> 01:38:17,875
Raya Gaji.

721
01:38:26,500 --> 01:38:28,417
Raya Gaji, my son.

722
01:41:08,957 --> 01:41:13,792
Vinyan SampannoItipiso Bhagava
Namo Budhaya. I set you free.

723
01:41:13,957 --> 01:41:15,873
I set you free.

724
01:41:15,957 --> 01:41:20,292
I set you free. I set you free.

725
01:42:38,042 --> 01:42:39,000
Long live the Emperor!

726
01:42:39,332 --> 01:42:40,625
Long live the Emperor!

727
01:42:43,917 --> 01:42:45,167
Long live the Emperor!

728
01:42:48,332 --> 01:42:49,667
Long live the Emperor!

729
01:42:53,000 --> 01:42:56,957
Long live the Emperor!
Long live the Emperor!

730
01:42:59,292 --> 01:43:01,375
Kimi

731
01:43:01,707 --> 01:43:04,042
Ga yo wa

732
01:43:04,457 --> 01:43:09,875
Chiyo ni
Yachiyo ni

733
01:43:10,125 --> 01:43:12,957
Sazare ishi no...

734
01:43:14,082 --> 01:43:17,582
I still remember what Luang Adul said
before I took this mission.

735
01:43:18,707 --> 01:43:19,792
He asked me...

736
01:43:21,250 --> 01:43:24,792
if I thought I could make a change.

737
01:43:27,417 --> 01:43:29,250
I don't have an answer for him.

738
01:43:31,082 --> 01:43:35,750
All I know is
if we don't have faith in our country...

739
01:43:35,957 --> 01:43:38,748
-Long live the Emperor!
-...we have nothing left...

740
01:43:38,832 --> 01:43:39,957
Long live the Emperor!

741
01:43:40,750 --> 01:43:42,707
...and we should have
enough courage

742
01:43:42,875 --> 01:43:45,250
-to protect it.
-Banzai! Banzai!

743
01:45:39,042 --> 01:45:42,207
If you promise to quit being a criminal
and to enter the monkhood,

744
01:45:44,332 --> 01:45:46,917
I'll capture you alive, Suea Bai.

745
01:49:24,875 --> 01:49:26,875
Subtitle translation by
Suganya Pankote

